<h1>British city has issued a parallel currency</h1>

<figure>
<img src="00.jpg"/>
</figure>

<p>
Mayor Peter Bristol Maine officially launched into circulation the local currency - the Bristol Pound, gaining a loaf of bread at a local bakery. About it writes The Financial Times. Bristol became the first city in the United Kingdom, which has got its own monetary unit. According to its purchasing power, it is the usual pound.
</p>


